          \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/home-assistant-featured-01.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/home-assistant-featured-01.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"5622\" height=\"3162\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Front view of the HiDoc H1 under a monitor\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/home-assistant-featured-01.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/home-assistant-featured-01.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n                \n                 \n                \t\n\u003ch5\u003e\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t        \t\t\t\t\n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/hidock-h1-review/\" title=\"HiDock H1 review: A docking station that boosts your meetings with AI\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\n\t\t\tHiDock H1 review: A docking station that boosts your meetings with AI\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eA promising addition to any workspace, the HiDock H1 falters too much to earn a full recommendation. But it\u0026#39;s still a cool idea.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"i-switch-between-devices-all-the-time\"\u003e\n                        I switch between devices all the time\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"keeping-my-peripherals-plugged-into-a-dock-saves-my-sanity\"\u003e\n            Keeping my peripherals plugged into a dock saves my sanity\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eI know my desk isn\u0026#39;t exactly typical, but more and more people now have multiple devices, especially if they have a personal computer and one issued by their employer. Keeping the two charged can be an issue depending on how many sockets you have nearby, and switching between the two means your brain and hands need to readjust to the ergonomic differences between them. \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eHowever, I sidestep those issues because everything I use is already plugged into the docking station. It\u0026#39;s not quite as friction-free as using a KVM, but changing one USB-C cable between devices is much simpler than deciding which of the half a dozen I can do without. \u003cspan\u003eNow, I can use the same peripherals I use on my desktop with whichever laptop(s) I\u0026#39;m testing at the time, and if I use something like \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/logitech-mx-anywhere-3s-review/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eLogitech Flow\u003c/a\u003e with a Logitech mouse and keyboard, I can even keep the docking station plugged into my desktop and control another computer.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch3 id=\"plus-it-means-i-can-use-my-pc-gaming-handhelds-in-desktop-mode\"\u003e\n            Plus, it means I can use my PC gaming handhelds in desktop mode\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/jsaux-rog-ally-x-dock-stand-11.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/jsaux-rog-ally-x-dock-stand-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/jsaux-rog-ally-x-dock-stand-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/jsaux-rog-ally-x-dock-stand-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/jsaux-rog-ally-x-dock-stand-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/jsaux-rog-ally-x-dock-stand-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/jsaux-rog-ally-x-dock-stand-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/jsaux-rog-ally-x-dock-stand-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/jsaux-rog-ally-x-dock-stand-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"2160\" height=\"1215\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Cables plugged into the back of the Jsaux multifunctional docking station.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/jsaux-rog-ally-x-dock-stand-11.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/jsaux-rog-ally-x-dock-stand-11.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI love using my \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/steam-deck-review/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eSteam Deck\u003c/a\u003e and other \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/best-pc-gaming-handhelds/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ePC gaming handhelds\u003c/a\u003e to catch up on my woeful backlog of games from wherever I am. But many tasks on the Steam Deck particularly need desktop mode to be accomplished, and that means I need a keyboard and mouse. Nobody has time to use the virtual keyboard for Terminal commands, and having a docking station available means I can blast through my configuration needs in no time while using a larger monitor to do so. They\u0026#39;re pretty capable for the odd document creation as well, if my main PC is in pieces to swap hardware or faulty parts.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n                \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"285c-44b2-99ee28a249f0\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/we-tried-gaming-handheld-docks-with-asus-rog-ally-x/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/rog-ally-x-docking-stations-featured.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/rog-ally-x-docking-stations-featured.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/rog-ally-x-docking-stations-featured.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/rog-ally-x-docking-stations-featured.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/rog-ally-x-docking-stations-featured.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/rog-ally-x-docking-stations-featured.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/rog-ally-x-docking-stations-featured.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/rog-ally-x-docking-stations-featured.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/rog-ally-x-docking-stations-featured.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"4480\" height=\"2520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"An Asus ROG Ally X surrounded by docking stations.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/rog-ally-x-docking-stations-featured.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/rog-ally-x-docking-stations-featured.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"it-39-s-a-quick-way-to-add-multiple-monitors\"\u003e\n                        It\u0026#39;s a quick way to add multiple monitors\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"no-laptop-makers-one-hdmi-output-is-not-enough\"\u003e\n            No laptop makers, one HDMI output is not enough\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eWhile many Windows laptops can connect to multiple monitors, Apple limits the display outputs of its Apple Silicon MacBooks depending on which chip you have. That makes having \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/docking-station-best-accessory-mac/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ea docking station a necessity for any Mac user\u003c/a\u003e, as long as that dock has DisplayLink connectivity. This allows it to send a video signal over standard USB connectors, increasing the number of monitors you can use and boosting productivity instantly.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch3 id=\"dp-alt-mode-over-usb-c-should-be-on-every-monitor\"\u003e\n            DP alt mode over USB-C should be on every monitor\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAlmost every laptop I\u0026#39;ve used recently has supported DisplayPort alt mode over USB-C, which is really handy for getting an image on an external display. Many monitors that support this method of connectivity also have power delivery down that port to the laptop, with the better models having 90W or above. But many monitors are still being released without USB-C as an input method, even though it really should be a standard connector by now.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n                \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"94b1-42a9-bc31d45a95ac\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/docking-station-best-accessory-mac/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/macbook-pro-m4-pro-feature.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/macbook-pro-m4-pro-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/macbook-pro-m4-pro-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/macbook-pro-m4-pro-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/macbook-pro-m4-pro-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/macbook-pro-m4-pro-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/macbook-pro-m4-pro-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/macbook-pro-m4-pro-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/macbook-pro-m4-pro-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"5015\" height=\"2821\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"16-inch MacBook Pro showing the XDA home page\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/macbook-pro-m4-pro-feature.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/macbook-pro-m4-pro-feature.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"docking-stations-are-really-a-necessity-for-the-home-office\"\u003e\n            Docking stations are really a necessity for the home office\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe change from USB-A to USB-C has only really happened on one side of the computing equation. Laptop makers have embraced the thinner port because it means they can shrink their devices. Desktop motherboards are adding more USB-C, but pushback from users has meant that USB-A is still prevalent. Until every peripheral is wireless, or I don\u0026#39;t need USB cables for another reason, I\u0026#39;m glad that I added a laptop docking station to my desk. It has helped me wrangle the cable clutter, added a few ports I rely on daily, and made it easy to switch between devices, something I used to dread. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
